Class PrintFile

  • java.lang.Object
    • PrintFile
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.awt.print.Printable

    public class PrintFile
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.awt.print.Printable
    This class is used to print the file. When constructed, it produces a dialog box that allows you to print to your printer correctly. Version Information:

    Author Oracle and its affiliates, Samantha Unger Version # 1 Date 05.27.16 Time Spent 2.5 hours

    Author Samantha Unger Version # 1.1 Date 06.08.16 Time Spent 2 hours What Was Changed Formatting of printed image was improved to make it more effective and compelling.

    Version:
    1.1 05.27.16

    Instance variables:

    names This String array is used to store the names to be printed.

    scores This String array is used to store the scores to be printed.

    levels This String array is used to store the levels to be printed.

    • Constructor Detail

      • PrintFile

        public PrintFile(java.lang.String[] newNames,
                 java.lang.String[] newScores,
                 java.lang.String[] newLevels)
        This is the method that prints the file. It constructs a BufferedImage and translates X and Y values to prevent clipping from outside the imageable area. Then, a try block is used while reading in a heading. Then, the heading and scores are drawn.
        Parameters:
        newNames - This String array is passed in as the new names associated with high scores.
        newScores - This String array is passed in as the new high scores.
        newLevels - This String array is passed in as the new levels associated with high scores.
